# List navigation aliases

`C-j` and `C-k` move down and up by one row, while `M-j` and `M-k`
jump to the last and first selectable rows in the session list.

    :bins jj cat

> [!NOTE]
> 'jj', and 'cat' are available.

    :copy tests/fixtures/jjconfig.toml .jjconfig.toml (copied)

    :t rename-session -t 0 runner (success)
    :t new-session -d -s alpha "cat" (success)
    :t new-session -d -s beta "cat" (success)
    :t new-session -d -s gamma "cat" (success)
    :t new-session -d -s zeta "cat" (success)
    :t new-session -d -s ui "sesh" (success)
    :t resize-window -t ui:0 -x 100 -y 12 (success)
    :pane ui:0.0
    :settle -d 2s (settled)

Hide the preview so the selected row movement is easy to inspect.

    :k C-p
    :snap

```terminal
session:                                                                                           ┃
  6/6 | [C-r] repo: none | [C-x] close, [C-f] flag                                                 ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
▌⬤ alpha                                                                                           ┃
 ⬤ beta                                                                                            ┃
 ⬤ gamma                                                                                           ┃
 ⬤ runner                                                                                          ┃
 ⬤ ui                                                                                              ┃
 ⬤ zeta                                                                                            ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
```

`C-j` moves the selection down by one row.

    :k C-j
    :snap

```terminal
session:                                                                                           ┃
  6/6 | [C-r] repo: none | [C-x] close, [C-f] flag                                                 ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
 ⬤ alpha                                                                                           ┃
▌⬤ beta                                                                                            ┃
 ⬤ gamma                                                                                           ┃
 ⬤ runner                                                                                          ┃
 ⬤ ui                                                                                              ┃
 ⬤ zeta                                                                                            ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
```

`C-k` moves the selection back up by one row.

    :k C-k
    :snap

```terminal
session:                                                                                           ┃
  6/6 | [C-r] repo: none | [C-x] close, [C-f] flag                                                 ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
▌⬤ alpha                                                                                           ┃
 ⬤ beta                                                                                            ┃
 ⬤ gamma                                                                                           ┃
 ⬤ runner                                                                                          ┃
 ⬤ ui                                                                                              ┃
 ⬤ zeta                                                                                            ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
```

`M-j` jumps to the last selectable row.

    :k M-j
    :snap

```terminal
session:                                                                                           ┃
  6/6 | [C-r] repo: none | [C-x] close, [C-f] flag                                                 ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
 ⬤ alpha                                                                                           ┃
 ⬤ beta                                                                                            ┃
 ⬤ gamma                                                                                           ┃
 ⬤ runner                                                                                          ┃
 ⬤ ui                                                                                              ┃
▌⬤ zeta                                                                                            ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
```

`M-k` jumps back to the first selectable row.

    :k M-k
    :snap

```terminal
